# Home Lab Setup Guide

## Hardware Requirements
1. **Computer/Server:**
   - CPU: Quad-core or better
   - RAM: 16GB or more
   - Storage: 500GB SSD/HDD or more

2. **Network Equipment:**
   - Router: Any modern router
   - Switch: 8-port Gigabit switch
   - Firewall: Optional, can use pfSense

## Software Installation

### 1. Install Virtualization Software
- **VMware Workstation/Player:**
  - Download and install from [VMware](https://www.vmware.com/products/workstation-player.html)
- **VirtualBox:**
  - Download and install from [VirtualBox](https://www.virtualbox.org/)
- **Proxmox VE:**
  - Download and install from [Proxmox](https://www.proxmox.com/en/proxmox-ve)

### 2. Set Up Networking
- **pfSense Firewall:**
  - Download pfSense from [pfSense](https://www.pfsense.org/download/)
  - Install on a dedicated machine or virtual machine

### 3. Install Operating Systems
- **Linux Ubuntu:**
  - Download from [Ubuntu](https://ubuntu.com/download)
  - Install on virtual machines
- **Windows Server:**
  - Obtain a license and install on a virtual machine

### 4. Configure Storage Solutions
- **FreeNAS/TrueNAS:**
  - Download from [TrueNAS](https://www.truenas.com/download-truenas-core/)
  - Install and configure on a dedicated machine or virtual machine

### 5. Set Up Configuration Management
- **Ansible:**
  - Install Ansible on your main machine
  - Create playbooks to automate tasks

### 6. Monitoring and Logging
- **Nagios:**
  - Download and install from [Nagios](https://www.nagios.org/downloads/)
- **ELK Stack:**
  - Follow installation guides from [Elastic](https://www.elastic.co/what-is/elk-stack)

